Kafka Interview Mastery Roadmap (2 hrs/day):

 ─── Week 0: Distributed Systems Prereqs ─────────────────────────

 Day 1-2: Fundamentals
  ☐ What is a distributed system and why we need them
  ☐ CAP theorem (Consistency, Availability, Partition tolerance)
  ☐ Eventual consistency vs strong consistency
  ☐ Latency vs throughput tradeoffs
  ☐ Horizontal vs vertical scaling

 Day 3-4: Replication & Partitioning
  ☐ Why replicate data (fault tolerance, availability)
  ☐ Leader-follower replication
  ☐ Synchronous vs asynchronous replication
  ☐ Data partitioning/sharding strategies
  ☐ Consistent hashing basics

 Day 5-6: Messaging & Communication
  ☐ Synchronous vs asynchronous communication
  ☐ Message queues vs event streams (pub/sub)
  ☐ Delivery guarantees (at-most-once, at-least-once, exactly-once)
  ☐ Idempotency — what it means and why it matters
  ☐ Backpressure concept

 Day 7: Consensus & Coordination
  ☐ Why consensus is hard (network partitions, failures)
  ☐ Leader election basics
  ☐ ZooKeeper — what it does (high level)
  ☐ Raft consensus (high level overview)
  ☐ Review: connect all concepts to why Kafka needs them

 ─── Week 1: Core Fundamentals ───────────────────────────────────

 Day 1-2: Architecture Basics
  ☐ What is Kafka and why it exists
  ☐ Brokers, clusters, and ZooKeeper/KRaft
  ☐ Topics and partitions
  ☐ Offsets and ordering guarantees
  ☐ Replication factor and leader/follower model
  ☐ Set up local Kafka cluster (Docker)

 Day 3-4: Producers
  ☐ Producer architecture and workflow
  ☐ Partitioning strategies (key-based, round-robin, custom)
  ☐ Acks (0, 1, all) and durability tradeoffs
  ☐ Batching and linger.ms
  ☐ Retries and idempotent producer
  ☐ Compression (snappy, lz4, zstd)
  ☐ Hands-on: Write a producer in your preferred language

 Day 5-6: Consumers
  ☐ Consumer groups and group coordinator
  ☐ Partition assignment strategies (range, round-robin, sticky, cooperative)
  ☐ Rebalancing — causes and impact
  ☐ Offset management (auto vs manual commit)
  ☐ at-least-once vs at-most-once vs exactly-once
  ☐ Hands-on: Write a consumer, test rebalancing

 Day 7: Review & Practice
  ☐ Revisit weak areas from days 1-6
  ☐ Draw architecture diagrams from memory
  ☐ Answer 10 basic Kafka interview questions

 ─── Week 2: Internals & Performance ────────────────────────────

 Day 8-9: Storage & Performance
  ☐ Log segments and log retention (time/size based)
  ☐ Log compaction (how and when to use)
  ☐ Page cache and OS-level optimizations
  ☐ Zero-copy transfer (sendfile)
  ☐ Sequential I/O and why Kafka is fast
  ☐ Segment indexing (.index and .timeindex files)

 Day 10-11: Reliability & Fault Tolerance
  ☐ ISR (In-Sync Replicas) deep dive
  ☐ Leader election process
  ☐ min.insync.replicas and unclean leader election
  ☐ Transactions and exactly-once semantics (EOS)
  ☐ Idempotent producer + transactional producer
  ☐ Consumer read_committed isolation level

 Day 12: Kafka Streams
  ☐ KStreams vs KTable
  ☐ Stateless operations (filter, map, flatMap)
  ☐ Stateful operations (aggregate, join, windowing)
  ☐ State stores and changelog topics
  ☐ When to use Streams vs Flink/Spark

 Day 13: Kafka Connect & Ecosystem
  ☐ Source and Sink connectors
  ☐ Schema Registry and Avro/Protobuf
  ☐ Kafka vs RabbitMQ vs SQS vs Pulsar
  ☐ Kafka on Kubernetes (Strimzi)
  ☐ AWS MSK overview

 Day 14: Review & Practice
  ☐ Revisit weak areas from days 8-13
  ☐ Practice explaining concepts out loud
  ☐ Answer 10 intermediate interview questions

 ─── Week 3: Advanced & Interview Prep ──────────────────────────

 Day 15-16: System Design with Kafka
  ☐ Event sourcing and CQRS patterns
  ☐ Design: real-time analytics pipeline
  ☐ Design: distributed log aggregation
  ☐ Design: event-driven microservices
  ☐ Design: CDC (Change Data Capture) pipeline
  ☐ Backpressure handling strategies

 Day 17-18: Operations & Troubleshooting
  ☐ Monitoring (consumer lag, under-replicated partitions)
  ☐ Common issues: consumer lag, rebalancing storms, disk full
  ☐ Partition reassignment and scaling
  ☐ Kafka security (SSL, SASL, ACLs)
  ☐ Tuning: throughput vs latency tradeoffs
  ☐ Multi-datacenter replication (MirrorMaker 2)

 Day 19-20: Mock Interviews
  ☐ Practice 5 "explain concept" questions
  ☐ Practice 3 "design a system using Kafka" questions
  ☐ Practice 3 "troubleshoot this scenario" questions
  ☐ Record yourself and review clarity
  ☐ Final weak-area review

 ─── Key Resources ───────────────────────────────────────────────

  ☐ Book: "Kafka: The Definitive Guide" (Ch 1-6 priority)
  ☐ Official docs: https://kafka.apache.org/documentation/
  ☐ Confluent blog and developer tutorials
  ☐ GitHub: conduktor/kafka-stack-docker-compose (local setup)

 ─── Top Interview Questions to Master ───────────────────────────

  ☐ How does Kafka achieve high throughput?
  ☐ Explain consumer group rebalancing
  ☐ How does Kafka guarantee ordering?
  ☐ What happens when a broker goes down?
  ☐ Exactly-once semantics — how does it work?
  ☐ Kafka vs traditional message queues — when to use which?
  ☐ How would you handle consumer lag in production?
  ☐ Explain log compaction and its use cases
  ☐ How does Kafka handle backpressure?
  ☐ Design a notification system using Kafka
